Does anyone know the cheapest way i can convert >350k sgd to usd  preferably seamlessly from my own uob account back to my own uob fx account?
ask your RM to quote you a negotiated rate... although i think SGD350k might not qualify.. do try though
Premier accounts etc might be better spread than fintech firms is it

if you do have Interactive Brokers  and you are also using it for Investments already  you could:1. Send SGD350k into IB.2. FX convert the SGD into USD for USD2 fee and get Interbank Spot FX Rate3. Remit USD out from IB to your UOB account (1 free TT out per month).
IBKR will take a few working days to get the USD out right?

Premier Accounts / Banks  even Private Banks  typically FX transactions cannot win IBKR FX transactions.Fintech firms must see which one... i think can't generally... some cheap some expensive  not all can remit USD out.

even if you do FX Spot  it wil settle T+1IBKR also works on a 'hold funds' basis  where funds remitted in must be withheld for 3 days before it can be withdrawn  but if you have sufficient Borrowing Power inside IBKR  you can withdraw the USD at T+1
